<div class="modal">
  <p>This is a visual representation of the infamous sin and cosine functions from that bullshit high school trig class wherein you were constantly asking yourself &quot;<strong>When the f*#k am I going to use this shit&quot;</strong></p>
  <p>The <span style="color: rgb(21, 40, 209);">blue</span> dot is the <strong>X</strong> coordinate mapping of the red dot (<strong>sin</strong>
      <meta charset="utf-8"><strong style="font-weight: 700; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;">(angle) * radius,
          <meta charset="utf-8"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">constantY</span></strong>)</p>
  <p>The <span style="color: rgb(34, 209, 21);">green</span> dot is the <strong>Y</strong> coordinate mapping of the red dot (
      <meta charset="utf-8"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Times; font-size: medium; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;">constantX,&nbsp;</span><strong>cos(angle) * radius</strong>)</p>
  <p>The <span style="color: rgb(219, 44, 29);">red</span> dot is the point <strong>(X, Y)</strong></p>
  <p>Side note, can you see if you can see how triangles show up? A better name for trigonometry could be the circular functions. Triangles are emergent though. </p>
